ng.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039156,0.07326,0.084314,0.094106,0.10004,0.099808,0.099903,0.094155,0.086631,0.085739,0.074153,0.068734],"unified_progress":[0.04553,0.057736,0.074027,0.083027,0.091271,0.10019,0.099143,0.09986,0.096959,0.095371,0.084644,0.072244]},{"section":10,"text":"The common triggers are foods, medications, or insect stings.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034448,0.070434,0.083368,0.092525,0.098148,0.10036,0.10064,0.09661,0.090143,0.09062,0.07696,0.065737],"unified_progress":[0.045129,0.066928,0.078787,0.086726,0.092657,0.098406,0.098647,0.09982,0.096201,0.094964,0.080126,0.06161]},{"section":11,"text":"Since he just tried an exotic food, that's the likely trigger here.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.051163,0.085163,0.088838,0.092108,0.092864,0.09497,0.090826,0.08952,0.084744,0.085917,0.074258,0.069629],"unified_progress":[0.084631,0.092215,0.08637,0.087411,0.087218,0.08784,0.086374,0.089089,0.083009,0.081203,0.072178,0.062461]},{"section":12,"text":"Let me think of other possibilities.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.32047,0.052102,0.052734,0.062276,0.064206,0.06377,0.062575,0.067632,0.068554,0.065813,0.069019,0.05085],"unified_progress":[0.22674,0.093555,0.063684,0.063826,0.074661,0.072101,0.088135,0.076855,0.073518,0.059835,0.055807,0.051277]},{"section":13,"text":"Could it be something else?","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.29518,0.05326,0.2714,0.059008,0.040779,0.038772,0.03563,0.041564,0.044575,0.044528,0.043526,0.031772],"unified_progress":[0.18135,0.061636,0.25343,0.083626,0.056259,0.05432,0.053098,0.061101,0.059666,0.049432,0.044622,0.041455]},{"section":14,"text":"Like a bacterial food poisoning?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03733,0.085884,0.084744,0.1116,0.11359,0.10005,0.097868,0.091451,0.083633,0.075985,0.067747,0.050116],"unified_progress":[0.04665,0.089564,0.086299,0.10845,0.10974,0.098862,0.095639,0.092863,0.086224,0.077659,0.064817,0.043233]},{"section":15,"text":"But food poisoning usually has more gastrointestinal symptoms like diarrhea, and the onset might be a bit delayed, not immediate.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022509,0.055743,0.072143,0.083105,0.092529,0.097388,0.10607,0.10788,0.10453,0.10055,0.09318,0.064384],"unified_progress":[0.03076,0.059701,0.075109,0.082287,0.096839,0.097885,0.10093,0.10794,0.10479,0.10758,0.085457,0.050715]},{"section":16,"text":"Plus, the breathing difficulty and swelling point more towards an allergic reaction rather than infection.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025311,0.057832,0.072479,0.082237,0.088734,0.093163,0.10057,0.10249,0.10144,0.10233,0.094852,0.078558],"unified_progress":[0.031226,0.054447,0.068302,0.078779,0.088365,0.094208,0.10164,0.10448,0.10507,0.10974,0.095297,0.068436]},{"section":17,"text":"Another thought: angioedema can sometimes be hereditary, but that's usually recurrent and not triggered by food.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027556,0.059182,0.07259,0.083503,0.092079,0.096987,0.10254,0.10373,0.10036,0.10099,0.089936,0.070542],"unified_progress":[0.036269,0.059382,0.074623,0.084648,0.093083,0.098862,0.10255,0.10504,0.10212,0.10295,0.084237,0.05624]},{"section":18,"text":"Since this happened after a new food exposure, anaphylaxis makes more sense.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039043,0.071067,0.078764,0.084978,0.089398,0.093101,0.094341,0.094789,0.092347,0.093952,0.085969,0.08225],"unified_progress":[0.061625,0.073943,0.076373,0.081526,0.085121,0.088885,0.091028,0.093499,0.091213,0.092311,0.086306,0.07817]},{"section":19,"text":"The combination of skin symptoms, airway swelling (leading to shortness of breath), and gastrointestinal symptoms (vomiting) fits the criteria for anaphylaxis.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033737,0.067453,0.075539,0.082159,0.088832,0.093947,0.097796,0.097625,0.095528,0.094207,0.090319,0.082857],"unified_progress":[0.042417,0.061642,0.071382,0.07733,0.08561,0.093611,0.094644,0.098161,0.099707,0.10047,0.09509,0.07994]},{"section":20,"text":"So the most likely diagnosis here is anaphylaxis due to a food allergy.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032553,0.056208,0.063451,0.069779,0.075072,0.07862,0.08441,0.087907,0.092845,0.098489,0.10613,0.15454],"unified_progress":[0.035398,0.039308,0.047986,0.057269,0.063156,0.075797,0.079496,0.09184,0.10068,0.1074,0.13394,0.16773]},{"section":21,"text":"The exotic food he consumed in Hawaii is probably the culprit, maybe something like a tropical fruit or shellfish, which he hasn't been exposed to before, leading to this severe allergic reaction.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038429,0.068831,0.073991,0.079989,0.086296,0.094522,0.094192,0.096154,0.095381,0.096918,0.090146,0.08515],"unified_progress":[0.068249,0.084134,0.076915,0.074941,0.078024,0.083262,0.083908,0.09171,0.091333,0.091772,0.091465,0.084288]}]}}